3 Difference with Python and Posit

Python and Posit (currently R) has different sytanx(the structure of statements in a computer language).
for loop example in Python:
for i in range(10):
  print(i)
for loop example in R:
for (i in 0:9) {
  print(i)
}
Python is an object-oriented programming language but R is a functional programming language.
Object-Oriented Programming Language Python
Functional Programming Language R
Python is a general-purpose programming language while R is a statistical programming language.
